1 in accordance with an agenda, plan, or resolution adopted by the United Nations or an
2 associated organization of the United Nations, without due process including:
3 a. Agenda 21;
4 b. The net-zero emissions plan;
5 c. The 2030 agenda for sustainable development; or
6 d. Any other international law or international plan of action that conflicts with the
7 United States Constitution or the Constitution of North Dakota.
8 3. This state or a political subdivision may not expend public funds or provide financial
9 aid to a nongovernmental or intergovernmental organization implementing a policy
10 relating to agenda 21, the net-zero emissions plan, the 2030 agenda for sustainable
11 development, or any other related plan or initiative.
12 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 23-12-21 of the North Dakota Century Code is
13 amended and reenacted as follows:
14 23-12-21. International health regulations.
15 A health-related regulation of an international health organization, either directly through the
16 organization or indirectly through law, regulation, or order of the federal government, is not
17 enforceable in this state unless enacted through legislation or a signed executive order.
18 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 23.1-01-15 of the North Dakota Century Code is
19 amended and reenacted as follows:
20 23.1-01-15. International climate control regulations.
21 A climate control-related regulation of an international organization, either directly through
22 the organization or indirectly through law or, regulation, or order of the federal government, is
23 not enforceable on this state.
